Question 1
Which of the following would you use to create a screen of nested composables in such a way that the elements stack up vertically?
Grid layout
Column layout
Row layout
Panel layout

Question 2
What is an Activity in Android UI Development? 
A function that performs a calculation. 
A component that allows users to interact with the app UI.
A special type of ViewGroup container. 
A resource file that stores application data. 

Question 3) What is an XML file used for in an Android project?
Defining a ViewGroup
Storing structured information
Styling a view

Question 4) What is the Activity lifecycle?
A function for determining the screen orientation
States an activity instance goes through from start to termination
A collection of callback methods
A method of placing an activity’s content

Question 5) Which of the following are examples of view groups? Select all that apply. 
RelativeLayout
LinearLayout
FrameLayout
GridViewLayout

Question 6) What is a Composable in Android UI Development? 
An animation used to transition between activities 
A library of user interface components.
A reusable component in Jetpack Compose. 

Question 7) Which of these is a way to preview the appearance of an Android UI?
Use the Android Studio Debugger.
Use the Android Studio Layout Editor.
Use the Android Studio Emulator.

Question 8) Which of the following is an Invisible UI element that acts as a container to other views?
View group
A tree
View
Layout

Question 9) Which of the following correspond to the attributes of XML elements?
Layouts
View groups
View Subclasses
Object properties

Question 10) Which of the following lays out composables horizontally?
Box
View
Column
Row

*******Answer**********

Question 1) Column layout
Question 2) A component that allows users to interact with the app UI.
Question 3) Storing structured information
Question 4) States an activity instance goes through from start to termination
Question 5) RelativeLayout
            LinearLayout
            FrameLayout
Question 6) A reusable component in Jetpack Compose
Question 7) Use the Android Studio Layout Editor
Question 8) View group
Question 9) Object properties
Question 10) Row
